Nicholas DeBenedictis

Age : 71Public asset : 5,051,888 USDLinked companies :  Exelon Corporation -  Aqua America Inc -  P H Glatfelter Co -  Mistras Group Inc 





Summary 



Mr. Nicholas DeBenedictis is Chairman at Philadelphia Convention & Visitors Bureau, Inc., Non-Executive Chairman at Aqua America, Inc., Chairman at Aqua North Carolina, Inc. and President at The Pennsylvania Society.He is on the Board of Directors at United Way of Greater Philadelphia & Southern New Jersey, MISTRAS Group, Inc., Commonwealth Edison Co., Exelon Corp., P.H. Glatfelter Co., Drexel University, Independence Blue Cross LLC, Independence Health Group, Inc., Independence Visitor Center Corp., Pennsylvania Environmental Council, Pennsylvania Partnership for Economic Education, Philadelphia Health & Education Corp., Philadelphia Hospital Education Foundation and Provident Mutual Life Insurance Co. Mr. DeBenedictis was previously employed as President by Philadelphia Suburban Water Co., President by Greater Philadelphia Chamber of Commerce, Secretary by Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Resources, Chairman & Chief Executive Officer by Aqua Pennsylvania, Inc., President by National Association of Water Cos., Member-Policy Committee by Pennsylvania Business Council, Chairman by Pennsylvania Business Roundtable, Member-Advisory Board by PNC Bank, NA (Investment Management), and a Principal by United States Environmental Protection Agency.He also served on the board at Met-Pro Corp., Harleysville Mutual Insurance Co., PECO Energy Co. and Pennsylvania Department of Community & Economic Development.He received his undergraduate degree from Drexel University and a graduate degree from Drexel University.



